English

[edit]
English Wikipedia has an article on:
Zwilling
Wikipedia

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from German Zwilling.

Proper noun

[edit]

Zwilling (plural Zwillings)

  1. A surname from German.

Statistics

[edit]
  • According to the 2010 United States Census, Zwilling is the 35866th most common surname in the United States, belonging to 626 individuals. Zwilling is most common among White (96.96%) individuals.

Further reading

[edit]
  • Hanks, Patrick, editor (2003), “Zwilling”, in Dictionary of American Family Names, volume 3, New York: Oxford University Press, →ISBN.

German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Middle High German zwillinc, zwinelinc, from Old High German zwiniling from an original *twiniling, from Proto-Germanic *twinilingaz, from *twinaz + *-lingaz.

Compare Dutch tweeling, English twinling, Danish tvilling. More at twin.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈt͡svɪlɪŋ/
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)
  • Hyphenation: Zwil‧ling

Noun

[edit]

Zwilling m (strong, genitive Zwillinges or Zwillings, plural Zwillinge, feminine Zwillingin)

  1. twin (male or female; the feminine form Zwillingin is rare)
  2. (in compounds) twin (used as a component in numerous compound words such as Zwillingstürme (“Twin Towers”), with (one or more) or without hyphens depending on the word's length and the taste of the writer)

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Zwilling [masculine, strong]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative ein der Zwilling die Zwillinge
genitive eines des Zwillinges, Zwillings der Zwillinge
dative einem dem Zwilling, Zwillinge1 den Zwillingen
accusative einen den Zwilling die Zwillinge

1Now rare, see notes.

Hunsrik

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Middle High German zwilling, zwinling, from Old High German zwiniling, from Proto-West Germanic *twiniling, from Proto-Germanic *twinilingaz.[1]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈt͡sviliŋ/
  • Rhymes: -iliŋ
  • Hyphenation: Zwil‧ling

Noun

[edit]

Zwilling m (plural Zwilling)

  1. twin
    Sie hon Zwilling kreid ― She had twins
    Meer sin Zwilling ― We are twins

References

[edit]
  1. ^ Boll, Piter Kehoma (2021), “Zwilling”, in Dicionário Hunsriqueano Riograndense–Português, 3rd edition (overall work in Portuguese), Ivoti: Riograndenser Hunsrickisch, page 183

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈt͡swiliŋ/

Noun

[edit]

Zwilling m (plural Zwillingen)

  1. twin
  2. Gemini (constellation and astrological sign)
